  "texts": [
    "Notably, the frequency of financial references picked up considerably after the Global Financial Crisis (GFC) and has only recently receded.",
    "Similarly, references to climate change have recently gained traction in central bank communication from 2016 onwards, in line with known trends.",
    "0.0 0.1 0.2 0.3 0.4 2000 2005 2010 2015 2020 Year Share topic Monetary Financial Macro International Fiscal Climate Other",
    "These topic frequencies differ strongly among sub-groups of countries (see Table 6).",
    "First, central bank officials of developing and emerging economies -following the classification of IMF (2023) -talk less about monetary topics, on average, and more about financial topics."
